{
  "stem": "10353.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She would smuggle me in some bread and I would smuggle out-- I would acquire some cigarettes and I would throw it through the fence to her.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she would throw me in some bread.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So for the little while, we could-- it made our life a little bit easier.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But for Christmas, the Swedish Blue Cross was very good and they sent packages, like little package with some Swedish crackers and little things like-- it wasn't very much.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was a package here was given for 16 people, a package like that.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But life was deteriorating, because people were starting to lose their strength.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And-- and the worst thing was that every morning at 6 o'clock, we had to be out in the cold for they called it appell, which is a roll call.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Now, then the Germans would come and make a head count.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that was one of the worst things, because in northern Germany, it was bitter cold, bitter cold.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we're standing there in that freezing subzero cold from 6 o'clock in the morning.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And god forbid if you were found to be-- to be left in the barrack, in the barrack, that you didn't come out, that-- it was a horrible punishment.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] He would come at 8 o'clock, at 9 o'clock, at 10 o'clock, at 11 o'clock.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And in the meantime, everybody was standing there in freezing cold and you-- you weren't allowed to move.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And-- and that-- and during that procedure, many, many people dropped dead, just dropped dead.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They just dropped, you know, like flies and you hauled them away.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] Famine started to set in very strongly.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "People became weaker and weaker.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And primarily the older people, they-- they couldn't move about.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They didn't go-- there was no soap.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "There was no towels.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "There was nothing.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "There was no toilet paper.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So what you did, you know, it was sandy terrain.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You went to the cold washbasins there, whatever they had there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So you took a handful of sand and you washed your-- instead of soap, you used sand.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And if you went to the-- you had to go to the washroom, you tore out a piece of your-- of your clothing and-- because there was no toilet paper.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And you used that and you washed it, you know.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And you washed it time and again.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You couldn't find a piece of paper if your life depended on it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then people were also infected with lice, but infected, you know, where you could be standing with a person and seeing crawling lice-- lice on them, and-- although there was an order that every day you had to stay in the barrack for an hour, an hour and a half-- they called it [INAUDIBLE] to-- to get-- them. but you couldn't.",
      "word_count": 62
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And famine became so very strong that you could be talking to a person [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] eyeball-to-eyeball in one minute.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in the next minute, he would just turn his eyes over and drop dead.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That's-- that's how weak people became.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The first-- the first notion that we got of what was going on was in March of 1944.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The American Air Force dropped some leaflets telling us about the Yalta Conference and the proximity of where the front line is standing.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But the SS hurriedly went around and they tried to scoop up the leaflets so we wouldn't know.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
